Cohort construction

We loaded the cohort extracted directly using SQL, then the cohort table was joined with other views with SOFA score, Elixhauser score, past history table that associated with our problem, and 30-day mortality information. We also defined platelet drop rate and plate nadir groups here.

basic <- read.csv("../data/iabp_medi.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
patient_list <- basic[, 'subject_id']

# sofa score (by mmg)
s = dbReadTable(con, "sofa")
s = s[, c(1, 2, 4)]
s = s[s$subject_id %in% patient_list, ]
s = s[!duplicated(s$subject_id, fromLast = TRUE), ]

# elixhauser score (https://raw.githubusercontent.com/MIT-LCP/mimic-code/master/concepts/comorbidity/elixhauser-ahrq-v37-with-drg.sql)
elix = dbReadTable(con, "elixhauser_ahrq_score")
elix = elix[, c(1:3)]
elix = elix[elix$subject_id %in% patient_list, ]
elix = elix[!duplicated(elix$subject_id, fromLast = TRUE), ]

# selected history (from history.sql)
e = dbReadTable(con, "elixhauser_ahrq_no_drg")
e = e[, c(1:7, 11)]
e = e[e$subject_id %in% patient_list, ]
e = e[!duplicated(e$subject_id, fromLast = TRUE), ]

# 30-day mortality
mort = dbGetQuery(con, "select a.subject_id, a.hadm_id, DATE_PART('day', p.dod - a.admittime) AS hosp_surv_days from admissions a  INNER JOIN patients p ON a.subject_id = p.subject_id")
mort = mort[mort$subject_id %in% patient_list, ]
mort$m30 = ifelse(mort$hosp_surv_days >= 30 | is.na(mort$hosp_surv_days), 0, 1)

# table join
basic = merge(basic, e, by=c("subject_id", "hadm_id"), all.x=T)
basic = merge(basic, s, by=c("subject_id", "hadm_id"), all.x=T)
basic = merge(basic, elix, by=c("subject_id", "hadm_id"), all.x=T)
basic = merge(basic, mort, by=c("subject_id", "hadm_id"), all.x=T)
for (i in 25:37) {
  basic[, i] = ifelse(is.na(basic[, i]), 0, basic[, i]) # problematic
}
for(i in c(15,17,23,24,38,39)){
  basic[, i] = ifelse(is.na(basic[, i]), mean(basic[, i], na.rm = TRUE), basic[, i]) # problematic
}

# define platelet drop rate
basic$plt_drop = (basic$plt - basic$plt_minvalue) / basic$plt
basic$plt_drop_grp <- cut2(basic$plt_drop, c(0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8))

basic$plt_nadir = cut2(basic$plt_minvalue, c(20, 50, 100))
basic$plt_nadir = factor(basic$plt_nadir, levels=rev(levels(basic$plt_nadir)))
#write.csv(basic, "../data/iabp.csv")

We planned to extract surgical history features form notes but discarded this idea since there were only five patients with narative information of surgery in the texts.

Figure 2a: Mortality rate in different groups (drop)

plt_sum <- basic %>% filter(!is.na(plt_drop_grp)) %>%
  group_by(plt_drop_grp) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(n=n(), medianHospLOS=median(los_hospital,na.rm=T),
                   mortHospRate=mean(hospital_expire_flag), mortHospSE=sqrt(mortHospRate*(1-mortHospRate)/n))

error.bar <- function(x, y, upper, lower=upper, length=0.1,...){
  if(length(x) != length(y) | length(y) !=length(lower) | length(lower) != length(upper))
  stop("vectors must be same length")
  arrows(x,y+upper, x, y-lower, angle=90, code=3, length=length, ...)
}

barx <- barplot(plt_sum$mortHospRate, names.arg=plt_sum$plt_drop_grp, ylim=c(0,0.65), col="yellow", axis.lty=1, xlab="Platelet drop group", ylab="Hospital mortality")
error.bar(barx, plt_sum$mortHospRate, plt_sum$mortHospSE)

Modeling: hospital mortality as the outcome variable (drop)

We applied multivariate logistic regression to calculate the odds ratios of features. Since we have limited patiens in our cohort, it doesnt make sense to include too many variables for modeling. This we either use LASSO or stepwise selection to reduce the feature number.

basic$plt_drop_grp <- as.factor(ifelse(is.na(basic$plt_drop_grp), 0, basic$plt_drop_grp))

test <- basic[t, ]

pred <- predict(model, test[, c("gender", "age", "bmi", "cad", "sofa", "elixhauser_vanwalraven", "plt_drop_grp")], type="class")
